OL,3,GNorth West
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FA rather cloudy morning with
OL,6,Fsome patchy light rain or drizzle,
OL,7,Fmainly over the hills. The cloud will
OL,8,Ftend to thin during the afternoon,
OL,9,Fespecially in the south allowing some
OL,10,Fbright or sunny spells to develop.
OL,11,FMild but breezy.
OL,12,
OL,13,CTonight:FOften cloudy in the north and
OL,14,Falong Irish Sea coasts with some
OL,15,Fpatchy drizzle. Dry elsewhere with
OL,16,Fclear spells. A mild night for most,
OL,17,Falthough locally chilly in sheltered
OL,18,Fspots.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
